==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monkery
<hw>Monk"er*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Monkeries</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The life of
monks; monastic life; monastic usage or customs; -- now usually applied
by way of reproach.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Miters, and wretched dead mediaeval <qex>monkeries</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A collective body of monks.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Though he have a whole <qex>monkery</qex> to sing for him.</q>
<rj><qau>Latimer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monkey</ent>⟦br⟧
